    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Upgrade PostgreSQL 9.3 to 9.4 on Mater-slave Replication Cluster]]></title>
    <link href="http://dbcaptain.com/blog/2015/10/30/Upgrade%20PostgreSQL%209.3%20to%209.4%20on%20mater-slave%20replication%20cluster/"/>
    <updated>2015-10-30T16:43:15+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://dbcaptain.com/blog/2015/10/30/Upgrade PostgreSQL 9.3 to 9.4 on mater-slave replication cluster</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3>Preparations:</h3>

<ol>
<li>backup DB cluster</li>
<li>backup config:</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>mkdir ~/pg_config_backup
</span><span class='line'>sudo cp /etc/postgresql/9.3/main/* ~/pg_config_backup</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>  <br/>
3. add extra package if missing:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>sudo apt-get update
</span><span class='line'>sudo apt-get install postgresql-server-dev-9.3</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<ol>
<li>check correct repository setup:</li>
</ol>


<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>echo "deb http://apt.postgresql.org/pub/repos/apt/ wheezy-pgdg main" &gt;&gt; /etc/apt/sources.list.d/pgdg.list
</span><span class='line'>sudo apt-get install wget ca-certificates
</span><span class='line'>wget --quiet -O - https://www.postgresql.org/media/keys/ACCC4CF8.asc | sudo apt-key add -</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Install 9.4 packages and create the new cluster:</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>sudo apt-get update
</span><span class='line'>sudo apt-get install postgresql-9.4 postgresql-contrib-9.4 postgresql-client-9.4 postgresql-9.4-pgespresso postgresql-server-dev-9.4</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Drop 9.4 cluster if created by installer</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>pg_dropcluster 9.4 main</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>cd /etc/postgresql
rm -rf 9.4
cp -R 9.3/ 9.4</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>change config to 9.4</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sed -i &rsquo;s/9.3/9.4/g' postgresql.conf
grep &lsquo;9.&rsquo; postgresql.conf</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>Initialize the new PostgreSQL 9.4 cluster:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo chown -R  postgres.postgres /etc/postgresql
sudo chown -R  postgres.postgres /data/postgresql
sudo su postgres
pg_createcluster -e UTF8 -p 5433 -d /data/postgresql/9.4/main 9.4 main</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>start:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>pg_ctlcluster 9.4 main start</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>check:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>postgres=# select datcollate, datctype from pg_database where datname = &lsquo;template0&rsquo;;
 datcollate  |  datctype <br/>
&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;-+&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;-
 en_US.UTF-8 | en_US.UTF-8
(1 row)
^D</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### stop running clusters</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo pg_lsclusters
sudo service postgresql stop
sudo mv /etc/init.d/postgresql /etc/init.d/postgresql.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### run pg_upgrade</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>cd /tmp</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>check:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo -H -u postgres /usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/bin/pg_upgrade \
   -b /usr/lib/postgresql/9.3/bin \
   -B /usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/bin \
   -d /data/postgresql/9.3/main \
   -D /data/postgresql/9.4/main \
   -o &lsquo; -c config_file=/etc/postgresql/9.3/main/postgresql.conf&rsquo; \
   -O &lsquo; -c config_file=/etc/postgresql/9.4/main/postgresql.conf&rsquo; \
   -p 5432 \
   -P 5433 \
   &ndash;check \
   &ndash;verbose \
   &ndash;retain</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>execute:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo -H -u postgres /usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/bin/pg_upgrade \
   -b /usr/lib/postgresql/9.3/bin \
   -B /usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/bin \
   -d /data/postgresql/9.3/main \
   -D /data/postgresql/9.4/main \
   -o &lsquo; -c config_file=/etc/postgresql/9.3/main/postgresql.conf&rsquo; \
   -O &lsquo; -c config_file=/etc/postgresql/9.4/main/postgresql.conf&rsquo; \
   -p 5432 \
   -P 5433 \
   &ndash;verbose \
   &ndash;retain \
   &ndash;jobs=4</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### change 9.4 port to 5432</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo sed -i &rsquo;s/5433/5432/g' /etc/postgresql/9.4/main/postgresql.conf
sudo sed -i &rsquo;s/5432/5433/g' /etc/postgresql/9.3/main/postgresql.conf</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>remove /var/lib/postgresql/9.4/main</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo mv /etc/init.d/postgresql. /etc/init.d/postgresql
pg_ctlcluster 9.4 main start</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### (optioanl) Remove the old packages</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>dpkg -l | grep postgresql
apt-get remove postgresql-9.3 postgresql-client-9.3 postgresql-contrib-9.3</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### Analyze and drop old</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo su  postgres
/tmp/analyze_new_cluster.sh
or /usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/bin/vacuumdb -dbluevine -Upostgres -h127.0.0.1
/tmp/delete_old_cluster.sh</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>### On slave:
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>backup configs:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>mkdir ~/pg_config_backup
sudo cp /etc/postgresql/9.3/main/* ~/pg_config_backup</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>Install 9.4 packages and create the new cluster:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install postgresql-9.4 postgresql-contrib-9.4 postgresql-client-9.4 postgresql-9.4-pgespresso postgresql-server-dev-9.4
pg_dropcluster 9.4 main &ndash;stop
mkdir  /data/postgresql/9.4/main
sudo chown -R  postgres.postgres /data/postgresql
cd /etc/postgresql
rm -rf 9.4
cp -R 9.3/ 9.4</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### On master:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>psql -U postgres -c &ldquo;select pg_start_backup(&lsquo;clone&rsquo;,true)&rdquo;
rsync -av &ndash;exclude pg_xlog &ndash;exclude postgresql.conf &ndash;exclude postgresql.pid \
     /data/postgresql/9.4/*  $SLAVE_HOST:/data/postgresql/9.4/
psql -U postgres -c &ldquo;select pg_stop_backup()&rdquo;
rsync -av /data/postgresql/9.4/main/pg_xlog $SLAVE_HOST:/data/postgresql/9.4/main/</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>### ON slave:
</span><span class='line'>recovery.conf in /data/postgres/9.4/main should look like this:</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>standby_mode = &lsquo;on&rsquo;
primary_conninfo = &lsquo;host=$MASTER_HOST port=5432 user=replicator password=bvmyreplpasserfvgty sslmode=require&rsquo;
trigger_file = &lsquo;/tmp/postgresql.trigger&rsquo;
```
sudo service postgresql start</p>

<h3>On master:</h3>

<p>sudo -u postgres psql -x -c &ldquo;select * from pg_stat_replication&rdquo;
sudo -u postgres psql -x -c &ldquo;select x id, x::text into test from generate_series(1, 1000000) x&rdquo;</p>

<p>check table exists on slave servers
check logs on all the servers</p>

<p><a href="http://www.depesz.com/2015/02/27/how-to-pg_upgrade/">http://www.depesz.com/2015/02/27/how-to-pg_upgrade/</a>
<a href="http://www.gab.lc/articles/migration_postgresql_9-3_to_9-4">http://www.gab.lc/articles/migration_postgresql_9-3_to_9-4</a>
<a href="http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/static/upgrading.html">http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/static/upgrading.html</a>
<a href="http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/static/pgupgrade.html">http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/static/pgupgrade.html</a>
<a href="https://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/Using_pg_upgrade_on_Ubuntu/Debian">https://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/Using_pg_upgrade_on_Ubuntu/Debian</a>
<a href="https://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/Binary_Replication_Tutorial">https://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/Binary_Replication_Tutorial</a></p>
]]></content>
